/mentioned>? Сюда же <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/><w>δəvity</w><gloss><q>красть</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II 521</biblScope></bibl>; ср. <bibl><ref target="#ref_Morgenstierne._EVP"/><biblScope>15</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 50, 87</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>59</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="iir"><lang/><w>dabh-</w></mentioned>. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>dab-</w><gloss><q>betray</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>dabh (dabhnoti)</w><gloss><q>do harm to smb</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>betray</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>dava-</w><gloss><q>beast of prey</q></gloss></mentioned>? Also here <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/><w>δəvity</w><gloss><q>steal</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II 521</biblScope></bibl>; cf. <bibl><ref target="#ref_Morgenstierne._EVP"/><biblScope>15</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 50, 87</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>59</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>